course provides an overview of china's engagement with countries in all regions and on a wide range of issues since it launched the policy of opening and reform in 1978 the goal is to provide a broad overview and systematic comparisons across regions and issues and to examine how china's global engagement has changed over time downloads pdf+ syllabus modified january 2012 pdf ips_246_syllabus_1 9 12 pdf 138.7 kb level graduate units 3 5 department international policy studies school of humanities and sciences search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
